laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is normal in shape and contour with normal echogenicity. No focal hepatic lesions. The main portal vein is patent with normal hepatopetal flow. Mild intrahepatic biliary duct dilation. The common bile duct measures 5 mm with multiple small stones, measuring up to 3 mm, within the common bile duct. The common bile duct cannot be visualized all the way to the pancreatic head. Within the gallbladder, there are multiple small stones, nearly filling the entire gallbladder, with the largest stone at the neck measuring up to 10 mm. No gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid.
